Let me read the referenced documentation and the relevant code files for the `pi install` command.

Now I have a clear picture of the issue. Let me summarize my analysis:

## Issue #1216 Analysis: Support installing local extension using `pi install`

### Summary
Feature request to allow `pi install /path/to/local/package` for local file paths. Currently only npm and git sources are supported.

### Current Behavior
In `package-manager.ts`, the `install()` method only handles `npm` and `git` types:

```typescript
async install(source: string, options?: { local?: boolean }): Promise<void> {
    const parsed = this.parseSource(source);
    // ...
    if (parsed.type === "npm") {
        await this.installNpm(parsed, scope, false);
        return;
    }
    if (parsed.type === "git") {
        await this.installGit(parsed, scope);
        return;
    }
    throw new Error(`Unsupported install source: ${source}`);
}
```

The `parseSource()` function already correctly identifies local paths (anything not npm/git returns `{ type: "local", path: source }`), but `install()` throws an error for this type.

### Proposed Fix

**File: `packages/coding-agent/src/core/package-manager.ts`**

1. In `install()` method (around line 475), add handling for local sources:
```typescript
if (parsed.type === "local") {
    const resolved = this.resolvePath(parsed.path);
    if (!existsSync(resolved)) {
        throw new Error(`Path does not exist: ${resolved}`);
    }
    // Local paths don't need installation - they just get added to settings
    // (which happens in main.ts after install() returns)
    return;
}
```

2. In `remove()` method (around line 490), add handling for local sources:
```typescript
if (parsed.type === "local") {
    // Local paths are just removed from settings, not deleted from disk
    // (which happens in main.ts after remove() returns)
    return;
}
```

**File: `packages/coding-agent/docs/packages.md`**

Update the documentation (line 75) from:
> Local paths work in settings but not with `pi install`.

To:
> Local paths point to directories or files on your machine. They are added to settings without copying.

Add local path examples to the install command section:
```bash
pi install /absolute/path/to/package
pi install ./relative/path/to/package
```

**File: `packages/coding-agent/CHANGELOG.md`**

Add entry under `## [Unreleased]`:
```markdown
### Added
- Support for local paths in `pi install` and `pi remove` commands ([#1216](https://github.com/badlogic/pi-mono/issues/1216))
```

### Why This Works

The infrastructure is already in place:
- `parseSource()` already parses local paths correctly
- `resolveLocalExtensionSource()` already handles resource resolution from local paths
- `updatePackageSources()` in `main.ts` already adds any source string to settings
- No file copying/installation needed for local paths

The change is minimal: just validate the path exists and allow the install flow to continue, letting `main.ts` add it to settings.

